The paper discusses the development of polar coding, which is a technique for channel coding. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the use of sequential decoding, which falls under the sub-category cs.SI (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of low-complexity recursive operations, which could fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the use of coding for communication channels, which could fall under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
